g.text: - For the metadata, we can use a NoSQL database. Our metadata is loosely

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: structured, with few relations and the main query pattern being to fetch files by user.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - For the file upload we have the following solutions

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - Bad Solution: Storing on the server

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - Good Solution: Using a Blob Storage.

g.text: 2) Sync Action: For the automatic sync part we have two flows to understand.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - upload the changed files to remote

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - OS provides API to give information about local changes

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 3) There is a problem with the file upload part in the pre deep dive solution. The

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: maximum file limit that an API gateway allow is upto 10mb. hence it won't be possible to

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: upload large files in the current design.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - Solution: Instead of uploading raw byte file via the server We just send the metadata

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: and store it in the DB. Now we get a preSigned url from S3 and return it to the client.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Using this url we upload the file directly to s3.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 4) Chunks: So we upload the file data in chunks. When we pause and resume again we only

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: upload the chunks that have not been already uploaded. How do we check this.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - Solution: We use the concept of fingerprinting(Hash of the bytes)

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - another thing to take care of is how do we update the status. S3 gives confirmation

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: then the client tells the server and it verifies with the s3.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 5) We could also do compression & decompression of data for faster uploads.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 6) Delta Sync: So when a change is made to a file we don't want to download the entire file

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: and make sync of it. Instead we only patch the chunks that have changed.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 7) for the sync part we are doing polling based on the folder id.

g.text: to start applying new changes. This solution can be used for version control and audit trails.
